# Git Workflow

## Conventional commits

Format: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>`

### Types

| Type | Use case |
|---|---|
| `feat` | New feature lub significant addition |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `docs` | Documentation only changes |
| `chore` | Maintenance (deps update, config, file moves) |
| `refactor` | Code change neither fix ani feature |
| `test` | Adding tests, no production code change |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |
| `style` | Formatting only (no code logic) |
| `ci` | CI/CD changes |

### Scopes (dla tego repo)

| Scope | Use case |
|---|---|
| `phase-N` | Phase-specific work (e.g., `feat(phase-1):`) |
| `skills` | Skill implementations |
| `presets` | DESIGN.md preset systems |
| `multi-variant` | Multi-variant generator |
| `output` | File export protocol |
| `mcp` | MCP server |
| `llm` | LLM provider abstraction |
| `rules` | Cursor rules updates |
| `deps` | Dependencies |
| `setup` | Initial setup, fork, branding |

